folder: Water Street & Dover Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Water Street at the S.E. corner of Dover Street. Also shown is Dover Street, at, adjoining and east of the S.E. corner of Water Street. The corner building is a frame house.

April 13, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same; showing a closer view of No. 279.
1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York. Negative No. 9.

folder: Water Street & Dover Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Water Street, north from and including Dover Street. The Brooklyn Bridge crosses buildings at a point just north of Dover Street, and projects eastward over the East River. March 20, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

ASSUMING STREET TO BE NORTH AND SOUTH.

folder: Water Street & Dover Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Water Street, west side, south from the Brooklyn Bridge (overhead); the street on the far side of fence is Dover Street. Prominent buildings shown, are the Cities Service and the Bank of Manhattan.

March 20, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

ASSUMING STREET TO BE NORTH AND SOUTH
